column5: Hey folks after reading some replies to other newbies I have decided to introduce myself.  My names Bill, I live in the greater to onto area.  I love the outdoors with canoe camping my passion.  Fishing has always been enjoyable but not tops on my to do list when out there until the last 5 years.  I started to go out with friends for opening seasons of trout and pickerel and hit the odd salmon run.  I fish for trout, bass, pike and pickerel on a fairly regular basis, and unlike my user name states it's not always for food lol.  So far I enjoy reading  the positive feedback,  tips and reviews from the experiences many of you have had and look forward reading and learning more. Thanks for now... PE
Hi Bill, nice to meet you. You'll like it here.  Dan.
Welcome aboard, Bill. Looking forward to your input.
Welcome to the board, Bill!  That's the way to introduce yourself
Welcome Bill, nice intro, thanks for taking the time. Hope you like it here.
Welcome to the site.  I like to eat a walleye or two.
welcome aboard, you wont be bored here... always something new everytime and everyone is great.. have fun staying!...
Morning Bill.Coffee's on Enjoy your stay and welcome.  Paul
Wellcome bill, I'm also new to the site and this is my first post. Lots of useful info and friendly people here.
And welcome to you too, CC.
Welcome to our OFC Community. A great place for info from a great bunch of people.  Cheers !!!
Welcome, Welcome, Welcome.  This is a great site.  Tom.
